    <td></td>
    <td><pre>public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] numbers = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
        int sum = 0;
        for (int num : numbers) {
            sum += num;
        }
        System.out.println("The sum of the numbers is: " + sum);
    }
}</pre></td>
    <td><img src="JavaPros.png" alt="Java pros" width="550" height="450"></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Cons</td>
    <th>Verbose Syntax</th>
    <th>Extra Comments</th>
  <tr>
    <td></td>
      <td><pre>public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        long startTime = System.nanoTime();
        for (int i = 0; i < 1000000; i++) {}
        long endTime = System.nanoTime();
        System.out.println("Execution time: " + (endTime - startTime) + " nanoseconds");
    }
}</pre></td>
    <td><img src="JavaCons.png" alt="Java cons" width="550" height="450"></td>
  </tr>
</table>

<h2>
  <p style="color: #1a0080;"> Conclusion </p>
</h2>
<p>Java is a robust, platform-independent language with a strong emphasis on object-oriented programming and a vast ecosystem.</p>

